It is very likely that I can create more value by answering a coworkers question than by continuously coding for hours.

If I *need* uninterrupted work for hours, I have optimized the way I work for the wrong metrics.

I use TDD and can interrupt my work within seconds. &gt;

I'll finish my current line of code, and maybe add a quick comment to the file. I can even commit and push it to a WIP branch.
When I get back I see the failing test, and can quickly pick up the work again.

Here is a great video about this approach: https://t.co/UAQ0ZWHJDs &gt;

